    ("h1", "5. SYSTEM ANALYSIS AND DESIGN"),

    ("h2", "5.1 System Architecture"),
    ("p", "The BuyTogether application rigorously follows a decoupled Client-Server architecture, ensuring high maintainability and specific separation of concerns. The frontend React Single Page Application (SPA) operates entirely independently from the backend logic, retrieving and sending serialized JSON payloads via RESTful API endpoints. This decoupling fundamentally allows the backend Express server to potentially serve various other clients (like a React Native mobile application) without massive architectural rewrites. Interwoven into this REST architecture is the WebSocket layer; Socket.io establishes persistent, full-duplex TCP connections specifically for high-frequency, low-latency data transmissions such as live chat messages and instantaneous system-wide alerts."),

