    ("p", "The systematic workflows dictating user interaction have been heavily refined:\n• Property Browsing Workflow: A client initiates a search request based on highly specific parameters (e.g., location radius, budget limits). The Express backend rapidly executes complex database queries—often utilizing Mongoose aggregation pipelines—and returns a highly structured JSON array. The frontend instantly parses this data, simultaneously populating a descriptive list-view alongside rendering corresponding interactive geographic markers on the Leaflet-powered map interface.\n• Real-Time Communications Workflow: A buyer types a message and clicks transmit. The React frontend emits a strictly formatted 'send_message' socket event. The Node.js server intercepts this payload, immediately identifies the specific 'Dealership Group Room' the buyer is connected to, and broadcasts the event instantly to all other currently connected socket clients in that specific room.\n• Secure Payment Workflow: When a client initiates a financial transaction—such as a property reservation deposit—the frontend securely requests a unique 'PaymentIntent' from the backend. The server communicates directly with Stripe to generate a highly secure client secret token. The frontend Stripe Elements library then securely captures the user's credit card details within an isolated, PCI-compliant iframe, executes the charge against the client secret."),

